Leveraging the latest advances in web and mobile technology, their solution allows providers, healthcare organizations, and payors to easily track and monitor patient's progress in order to impropatients'es and minimize the need for costly hospital/surgical care for those whose condi or ions are not improving. ChronicWatch can help providers increase their revenue potential from CCM with minimal implementation and can easily be incorporated into a provider's daily workflow with a very clean solution for data exchange from and to electronic health records (EHR). Their solution also offers features that allow families and caregivers to indicate if there is evidence of worsening in a patient's condition, so that symptoms can be managed and further deterioration avoided. Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Fabbro Industries, LLC is a motorcycle R&D firm specializing in small production, high-quality manufacturing of motorcycles and motorcycle parts. The Type 57x™, Fabbro's flagship product, is a patented motorcycle frame (chassis) that removes the need for a pivot axle and integrates the rear suspension system directly into the existing frame members, freeing up .5 cubic-foot of space without changing the wheelbase dimensions. The Type 57x™ draws on the strengths of the three frames on the market - the rigid frame with clean lines and no suspension, and the swingarm and Softail frames with bulky suspensions and a less pleasing aesthetic - while eliminating their weaknesses. With the Type 57x™, riders no longer need to tradeoff between comfort and design, since the frame optimizes both form and function. The Type 57x™ caters specifically to the needs of the changing American motorcycle industry; those who want a nostalgic look, but also the convenience of today’s modern suspension components. It also frees up valuable space needed for emerging hybrid/EV technologies. Fabbro products are rooted in soul and crafted with excellence in New York.

Full Description: Sustainable Real Estate Solutions, Inc. provides on-demand energy and sustainability performance assessment and management software solutions for the commercial real estate industry. The company offers Sustainable Real Estate Manager platform, an Internet-based software as a service, which is used for monitoring building energy and water consumption and cost; automating key performance indicator analytics and reporting; tracking CO2 emissions performance; benchmarking internal and external peer buildings; comparing actual and budgeted performance; identifying no-cost/low-cost energy, water, and waste cost savings opportunities; monetizing hidden carbon assets; and facilitating compliance with energy and sustainability related disclosure, labeling, auditing, and construction regulations. Its platform enables building owners, operators, investors, lenders, tenants, and consultants to assess, benchmark, and optimize the energy and sustainability performance of individual properties and portfolios in the United States and internationally.  The company is based in Monroe, Connecticut.

Description: cloud computing enabler for CSPs
Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: Cloudwrangler™ is the cloud app store for small and medium businesses. With Cloudwrangler, businesses can find all the cloud services they need from one source, with one contract, one monthly invoice and one contact for technical support. And Cloudwrangler allows SMBs to monitor all their cloud services, licenses and users from one dashboard. Cloudwrangler is built and operated by Verecloud, Inc. Based in Denver, Colorado, Verecloud, Inc. is an innovative technology company that connects and integrates cloud service suppliers to small and medium size businesses (SMBs) through multiple distribution channels. Verecloud’s mission is to become the industry leader in cloud service brokerage by creating a value chain with the following benefits: SMBs can more efficiently operate their businesses by expanding and aggregating their cloud services through one portal. Cloud service suppliers can expand their reach and strengthen their product offerings through Cloudwrangler’s powerful integration and billing capabilities. Cloudwrangler™ bridges the current gap between (i) small and medium businesses that want expanded and integrated services via the Cloud, (ii) communications service providers (CSPs) and managed service suppliers (MSPs) who need innovative, high-margin services to drive growth, and (iii) innovative clouding computing solution suppliers who want access to the large distribution channels that have developed.

Description: Viderics is developing an ultrasound-based device to monitor at-risk cardiac patients continuously.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Viderics is developing a continuous transthoracic echocardiography (cTTE) system to acquire continuous, repeatable ultrasonic views of the heart without an attending sonographer. It will include software to calculate ejection fraction, stroke volume and cardiac output by analyzing the continuous stream of heart images. The system’s initial intended clinical application will be hemodynamic monitoring of patients at high cardiac risk in critical care, surgery, pre-op, and step-down care. The primary indication will be for patients unresponsive to standard care protocols and whose cardiac condition may change rapidly.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering, Software
